Dim sum was delicious 😋... Wonderful customer service 👏 👌. I did take out so I can't speak on the full dim sum experience but I thought the food was fairly priced. I will be back!

Meh. We got delivery.

Maybe 3 and 3/4 stars. But I’m going to be generous and forgive the mishap. I have to give it credit for recovery.  We ordered through door dash and the prices are too high for how much food they actually give you. So here is our rating. Well start with needs improvements to needs to sustain.  3 stars on the price: Too high for the amount of food they give you. We ordered seafood pumpkin soup and there’s only chopped up shrimp and chopped up scallops in a maybe 3 cups container for $20 I expected a variety of “seafood” if we must call it that. Otherwise it’s chopped shrimp and scallops.  2 stars on the fact that they gave us the broth for my daughters wonton noodle soup without the wonton or the noodles.  2 stars in the $24 dollar one cup of beef tenderloin with black pepper and onions. For $24 the beef tenderloin should’ve been flying but it didn’t taste special enough to only give us a cup of it for the price.  However, 4 stars on the flavors. The pumpkin noodle soup is surprisingly delicious.  The Lamb Stew with Bean Curd Casserole is also amazing.  The steamed chicken feet is also flavorful.  They also recover by sending us another batch of wonton noodle soup but 3 stars on the fact that I had to spend another $15 just so the door dash can deliver what they forgot on our order.  In that $15 4 stars on the coconut mochi.  That’s why this rating could’ve been 5 stars if they lower their prices slightly and not inconvenience their customers in forgetting their food.  The flavor I’d say makes up for it...a little!!
The food was good and service great.  Going to the parking garage, I saw how this guy used a glass tube and blow torch.
Best jook! 👍everything is fresh and they continue to bring out fresh items all the time.
Never tried it
Chicken. Feet. On. Fleek. Stuffed on literally $15 per person! Super quality for value.

Open on Sundays ! With indoor seating, too, during this coronavirus era. Friendly and efficient staff, and delicious dim sum 點心。  I loved my steamed shrimp dumplings with chives 鮮蝦餃, and the seafood bundles 海鮮紮. All very fresh and flavorful ; sometimes I could catch a glimpse of the chefs in the back preparing all the items.
They have the best diem sam !
It's air conditioned and clean!  But seriously, the food is great and the service is better than most!  Very friendly setting.

I loved it😁

Very expensive for dim sum. We had 5 people, didn't stuff ourselves, yet spent $96+tip. Food was generally good. Walnut shrimp, the various dumplings including soup dumplings were decent. Just not worth the price at all. There are better places in the area.

Great Dim Sum!  I would recommend this place and will continue to come here.  The only downside, it’s a small place and it’s  in Chinatown, so no parking except on the street or  in a municipal parking lot.
Lovely authentic chineese food. Very tasty.

Tried this place since a co-worker brought some dim sum at work. It was so good. Price is just about right. Restaurant location is near public parking - so not a problem accessing the place. Price is just about right. Food very tasty. The staff was so nice to hand me a menu with picture to make sure I am ordering what I really wanted. Try it and you wont be disappointed.

Good food and epic portions.  The night I was in here there was an OUT OF CONTROL large family party that was laughing and hollering in Chinese the whole time.  It was fun, and made the experience great.  Food was good, but a bit bland.  Don't be afraid to order something with an extra kick.  Portion was EPIC.

Decent dim sum.  Limited varieties in cart.  Most of dim sum are cook to order.  Not the best tasting dim sum.   No parking and does not validate parking..  Portion sizes were small.  Known for bait&switch such as replacing dishes with different kind of meat.  We order pork jowl (cheek) and replaced with regular cut of pork.  We knew right away because of the meat texture.  Shame on you Ginger.  Very sneaky.

I went with a few friends to enjoy a nice afternoon with some good dim sum and good company. However, the place wad highly disappointing. They try to forcr dimsum dishes onto your table, and during dimsum hours we were trying to order from the menue. We gad to ask multiple times for someone to come and take our order. It wasn't until 30 minutes aftet that we actually got to put our order down. To add on, the ordering was a mess! They got my order wrong even though I pointed directly to the order. When the order came, I told them it was wrong and they took it away to replace the order with the correct one. I had ordered Beef chow fun with black bean, pointed it out to the waiter yet he got it wrong! And when my correct order came, I took a bite of the beef, but it was undercooked! I decided to give up asking because they obviously could'nt understand me so my experience here was completely ruined. I feel like I have to write this review to save people some money and some time. If I could give 0 stars, I would. If you want to go to a good Chinese restaurant where you will not be disappointed, go to Happy Days in Kaimuki instead! Way better, service is great, and they are polite.
Smaller family style Chinese restaurant with good prices and tasty food. Loved the Abalone soup!!!
Small local dim sum restaurant with really good food.
Love the chicken feet.

I have come to this place for about 2-3 times. The food is good, and it is not super crowded (as far as I know). I think the price is decent, and the service is alright. Finding parking maybe the hardest thing to do.

We came after 1 and unfortunately it wasn't much left just warmed up yesterday's food. Not very fresh. Quite disappointed. We've been coming here for the past 10 years this time food not nice. Waiters River wonderful I wished I could say the same for the food.
Love this place Friendly staff, which is special for a dim sum place. Great prices

This is one of several dim sum restaurants we frequent. I like most but not all of their dim sum ... their pi is very thin (a good quality) and many of their fillings are excellent. The great: spinach with seafood, chives with shrimp; the good: har gow; the I've tasted better: siu mai, chicken feet. Dishes are $3.49 or $4.95 for 3 pieces. We order noodles...delicate but subtly flavored.  I tried their won ton soup once...the won ton were excellent, the broth too bland.
First time there .tryed the dim sum .very good  hard to find a table.(lunch time) other then that fast service.if you speak Chinese better yet.ill try it again
Great food and friendly, and attentive staff.
Very good dim sum and plate meals. Helpful, friendly staff. Really enjoyed eating here.

Visited here a few times, it's small, visually nice, and clean. The food is good; the service is a bit slow. BYOB no corkage fee, nice. Strictly menu meal selections only, no diversions or off menu meals allowed.  The disappointment came when they were busy, they were rude & angry towards us. Then they took the Chinese speaking customers behind us first. How sad.

I like dim sum and heard good things about this place. I was not really happy with their food. It was hard to chew the garlic fried rice because I think they overcooked the garlic. So it felt like I chew some rocks. All the other dishes were soso. Server was pretty friendly

Went for dim sum. The steamed pork buns were tasty, but sparce on meat. The sel mei were very good. The sesame balls were of varying sizes, and not crispy, maybe had been sitting out awhile. The custard tarts were not too sweet. My wife had beef w broccoli. Lots of food. Good value for the cost.

Went here today for first time, it will the last!  Disorganized, limited seating. Four tops placed in two long lines.  Asked to share late round table with strangers also waiting.  Limited choices, no vegetable dim sum choices.  At 12:00 and we had a choice of only five(5) hot items.  At 12:45 they were out of items, in our case custard tarts and we were told no more would be made. Check given but no indication that we were to pay at register or give to pay server.  Food was adequate but not outstanding

My mom introduced me to this place.  She goes there all the time. Sevice is meh even though we ordered in Cantonese.  It’s clean and decent for a hole in the wall joint.  Food came fast and was quite tasty to my surprise. A few “Bizzare Foods” I would recommend for the adventurous.   Sauté pork cheeks with lotus root, (a bit oily and spicy ) and the salted dried fish with chicken fried rice (fish is dried raw and for about 30 days).  Thanks mom.
Small dim sum restaurant with friendly staff and good authentic food.
Only had the dimsum which was delicious. Service was attentive. And food was delivered very quickly.
Taste of TimSum is 3/10 Score. Service is so EXPECTEDLY POOR...all she care is TAKING ORDER and started showing Attitude soon after I told her we just wanted 2 dishes as our after lunch treats...
dim sum is very doughy and cold.  help is very rude.
Generous size portions for sure! Good pricing and great tasting. We do takeout at least 2 times a month.

Generous size portions.  Excellent tasting food from menu.  The sweet and sour fish had lots of fish with minimal batter and the sauce was the best I've tasted outside of Hong Kong.  Tofu and spinach was also excellent vegetarian dish - large serving of spinach - and interesting preparation of tofu - not just plain tofu cut into squares as one usually gets in tofu dishes.  Service for the tofu dish was very slow - the fish dish very fast.
Exceptional dishes! Food was cooked with experienced and care.
Dim sum carts and menu items available. Dim sum was ok and a bit warm to cold. I prefer restaurants that make or steam their dim sum as they are ordered, steamy hot!
This is a very nice place that is clean and well kept with very friendly staff. The food is fantastic.  Dim Sum is some of the best I have ever had.  Highly recommend this place.

Small seating area. Tables in center of restaurant were joining each other. So groups were separated by leaving a vacant seat between the two.  Got offended when the waitress placed her tray on the table in the space between the separate group while taking order from the table next to us. Dishes were served hot. Had to wait to become cool enough to eat. Jin doing and custard is the tops. Not greasy or flakey. Jin dui had a nice crust to it, an the custard held it's shape during the entire consumption. Tripe was a little bland, and the sauce was overpowering. I would say the sauce was premade, and the tripe was blanched and mixed with the sauce. Shu Mai had small but firm, whole shrimp in it. Spare ribs was unremarkable, about the same as others. But it did lack bones. What it did have was tendon, which was surprisingly soft and edible. Would have mistaken it for fat if it wasn't for the crunchyness.
Lunch Dim sum service was prompt, the guy waiter was the best. Food was awesome!!! Try things off of the menu and not just the dim sum cart. Best we've had.

HORRIBLE service. I'm sure the food would've been good if we were able to order. We were ignored from the moment we walked in. Waited for a bit while servers walked by and ignored us, approached someone to get seated,  waited at a table for 10-15 min. while we watched a large group of 8-9 people get seated next to us, were brought water, tea, orders taken, and dim sum cart brought to them. Flagged someone down to get water, while we were brought random dim sum. After a 3 rounds of the server bringing random stuff we didnt really want but at that point too hungry to turn it away and not getting to pick we were done.
